<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - RADIATOR AND
        COMPONENT REMOVal - COOLING SYSTEM RADIATOR HOSE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>COOLING SYSTEM RADIATOR HOSE</title>
        <para>The International cooling system is fitted with heat shrink clamps on the radiator connections. A special
            type tool is required (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1200813">Figure 13</hotlnk>) for the removal of the Gates PowerGrip Shrink Band (SB) clamp.
            The recommended tool for this application is a heavy duty SB Clamp Removal Tool.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200813" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200813.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200813.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="152px"/>
            <caption>Figure 13. Heavy Duty SB Clamp Removal Tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Beginning on the driver side of the radiator, locate the radiator hose and Gates SB clamp (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200814">Items 1 and 2, Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200814" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200814.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200814.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Lower Radiator Hose</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GATES SB CLAMP</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Utilizing the SB clamp cutting tool, melt away clamp on the cooling system hose, driver
                side, closest to the radiator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The entire hose connection does not have to be removed to remove radiator. If the existing
                hose is to be replaced, the SB tool must be used on the opposite end of hose with SB clamp (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200815">Item 1, Figure 15</hotlnk>)
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200815" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200815.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200815.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Driver Side Engine Hose Connection</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GATES SB CLAMP</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate lower passenger side radiator hose and heat shrink clamp, and melt away heat shrink
                clamp (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200816">Item 2, Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200816" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200816.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200816.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Passenger Side Lower Cooling System Hose And Clamp</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GATES SB CLAMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SB CLAMP MELTING TOOL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. RADIATOR STAY ROD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Find and remove rear radiator hose clamp with SB tool.</para>
            <figure id="f1200817" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200817.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200817.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Passenger Side Rear Radiator Hose And Clamp Connection</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GATES SB CLAMP</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate and disconnect water heater hose from the mounting bracket on the passenger side of
                the radiator (if applicable). Heater hose return is routed to the engine after 07/22/2002 (refer to AFC
                G-02906).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure water heater radiator hose out of the way for access.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
